# ğŸ“‹ Audit Report Journal

This document stores manual audit results for system design, governance adherence, and implementation integrity.

---

## ğŸ” Audit Scope

Each audit verifies:

- That locked systems match their journal entry
- That implementation (if claimed) aligns with the specification
- That versioning, changelogs, and governance were properly followed

Audits may be:
- Manual (triggered by user)
- Automatic (e.g., before milestone or export)

---

## ğŸ§¾ Report Format

Each audit must contain:

- Timestamp
- Trigger type (manual, milestone, export)
- Summary of systems reviewed
- Deviations found (if any)
- Action items (e.g., relock, reimplement, re-audit)
- Auditor notes

